name: CMTremorResult
desc: A result object that contains data about the presence and strength of tremors during a one-minute interval.

items.name: var startDate: Date
items.desc: The result’s start time and date.

items.name: var endDate: Date
items.desc: The result's end time and date.

items.name: var percentUnknown: Float
items.desc: The percentage of time when the algorithm couldn’t make a determination.

items.name: var percentNone: Float
items.desc: The percentage of time when no tremor was detected.

items.name: var percentSlight: Float
items.desc: The percentage of time when a tremor was likely, and the displacement amplitude was slight.

items.name: var percentMild: Float
items.desc: The percentage of time when a tremor was likely, and the displacement amplitude was mild.

items.name: var percentModerate: Float
items.desc: The percentage of time when a tremor was likely, and the displacement amplitude was moderate.

items.name: var percentStrong: Float
items.desc: The percentage of time when a tremor was likely, and the displacement amplitude was strong.
